Showchar, its not as useful as the 'Ruler' procedure, but it makes its point and is eay to understand.
The Showchar program clears the sceen, displays a ruler on line 1, and below that shows a table containing 224 of 256 ASCII characters, neatly displayed in seven lines of 32 characters each. 
The table includes the "high" 127 ASCII characters, including foreign-language characters, line-draw characters, and miscellaneous symbols. 

The showchar program introdcues a couple of new concepts and instructions, all related to program loops. 
All procedures and macros it invokes are prestend in the program file. 
It also uses the following two equates not present in the program. 
	
	CHRTROW	equ 2		; Chart begins 2 lines from top of the display
	CHRTLEN	equ 32		; Each chart line shows 32 characters 

GO read the sample program "Showchar_sample_program.asm"
